WEBVTT

00:01.602 --> 00:05.373
[ Chuckles ]

00:05.406 --> 00:07.675
HERE.

00:07.708 --> 00:12.046
THE WOMAN IS SUPPOSED
TO BE HERE.

00:12.080 --> 00:15.316
- UH-HUH. IN THE CORRIDOR.
- THEN HERE.

00:15.349 --> 00:17.085
IN THE LIBRARY.
AND--

00:17.118 --> 00:19.187
IN THE CONFERENCE ROOM.

00:19.220 --> 00:22.656
IF YOU'RE TRYING
TO PICK MY POCKET,
YOU'VE GOT TO DISTRACT ME.

00:22.690 --> 00:26.260
YOU CAN'T STEAL A GUY'S
WALKIE IF HE'S THINKING
ABOUT HIS WALKIE.

00:26.294 --> 00:30.030
UH-HUH. P.S.
THAT'S NOT MY SPOT.

00:30.064 --> 00:33.534
THAT IS NOT MY SPOT.
THAT IS YOUR SPOT.

00:33.567 --> 00:37.438
AND THAT'S WHERE YOU NEED
TO BE SO THAT JONAS CAN MAKE
THE PASS TO THE WOMAN.

00:37.471 --> 00:41.041
AND JONAS CAN'T MAKE
THE PASS TO THE WOMAN
UNLESS YOU ARE THERE.

00:43.944 --> 00:46.814
OH.
HERE'S YOUR WALKIE.

00:51.285 --> 00:53.187
[ Chuckles ]
[ Woman ]
ALL EMBASSY EMPLOYEES--

00:53.221 --> 00:56.056
BOOTS AND SADDLES.

00:56.090 --> 00:59.127
THE FACILITY IS NOW--

00:59.160 --> 01:01.229
THE ATMOSPHERE
AND CONDITIONS REQUIRED...

01:01.262 --> 01:03.964
TO PASS HER THE TRANSMITTING
DEVICE, SHOULD SHE HAVE
ANY QUESTIONS.

01:03.997 --> 01:06.600
THE DEVICE
NEED NOT BE TURNED ON.

01:06.634 --> 01:09.137
IT WILL AUTOMATICALLY ACTIVATE
WHEN IT'S EXPOSED TO THE AIR.

01:09.170 --> 01:12.473
HERE IT IS TRANSMITTING.
HERE IT IS NOT.

01:12.506 --> 01:15.476
[ Bob ]
ALL PRESENT AND SOBER,
SERGEANT MAJOR.

01:17.145 --> 01:19.813
THESE WERE TAKEN
LAST NIGHT.

01:19.847 --> 01:22.483
TELL HER SHE MUST
PLANT THE DEVICE...

01:22.516 --> 01:25.753
WITHIN 10 FEET
OF THE IRANIAN AMBASSADOR
FOR US TO LISTEN IN.

01:25.786 --> 01:28.456
THE RECOGNITION SYMBOL?

01:28.489 --> 01:30.991
BECAUSE SHE'S SKITTISH.
SHE WON'T TALK
WITHOUT THE SYMBOL.

01:31.024 --> 01:34.328
OUR MAN OUTSIDE WILL BE
IN CONTACT WITH ME, AND SHOULD
YOU NEED TO COMMUNICATE--

01:34.362 --> 01:36.964
I DON'T THINK THAT WILL BE
NECESSARY, MA'AM. IN FACT,

01:36.997 --> 01:40.601
I RESPECTFULLY REQUEST
THAT HE SIT OUT.

01:40.634 --> 01:43.003
THANK YOU.
WELL, OUR MAN OUTSIDE...

01:43.036 --> 01:45.139
WILL BE IN CONSTANT
CONTACT WITH ME.

01:45.173 --> 01:48.576
AND SHOULD YOU WISH TO
COMMUNICATE DISCREETLY,
YOU MAY AVAIL YOURSELF OF HIM.

01:48.609 --> 01:51.111
THANK YOU, MA'AM.

01:52.880 --> 01:55.449
LET'S START OVER.

01:57.618 --> 02:01.655
I DON'T THINK WE KNOW ANYONE
WANTS THE IRANIANS
TO GET THE BOMB.

02:01.689 --> 02:04.592
WE KNOW ANYBODY LIKE THAT?

02:04.625 --> 02:07.127
I DON'T THINK WE WANT THEM
TO PURCHASE THAT TECHNOLOGY.

02:07.161 --> 02:09.830
[ Jonas ] NO, WE DON'T.
WE'RE ON THE SAME TEAM,
ARE WE NOT?

02:09.863 --> 02:13.367
- WE ARE ON THE SAME TEAM.
- AND YOUR TEAM IS UNDER
MY AGENCY'S CONTROL.

02:13.401 --> 02:15.669
UNDER C.I.A.'S CONTROL,
BUT MY TEAM'S ON THE FIELD.

02:15.703 --> 02:18.005
SERGEANT.

02:18.038 --> 02:20.474
I HEAR YOU.

02:26.214 --> 02:29.016
IT AIN'T ABOUT
SPOOKS VERSUS SHOOTERS.

02:29.049 --> 02:31.619
WE HAVE ONE OPPORTUNITY
TO LISTEN IN,

02:31.652 --> 02:34.188
TO DETERMINE IF OUR GALLANT
FRIENDS THE RUSSIANS...

02:34.222 --> 02:38.326
ARE GOING TO SELL IRAN
THAT TECHNOLOGY,
WHICH IN EFFECT IS THE BOMB.

02:38.359 --> 02:41.995
AND WHAT DO YOU THINK, MA'AM?
ARE OUR LITTLE FRIENDS AWARE
OF OUR INTEREST OR NOT?

02:42.029 --> 02:46.200
THEY ARE. WHICH IS WHY IT IS
IMPERATIVE WE HEAR WHAT
THEY MAY SAY IN PRIVATE.

02:46.234 --> 02:50.638
AND YOU TELL ME
THIS WOMAN IS SKITTISH.
I WILL PASS THE DEVICE.

02:50.671 --> 02:54.308
BEFORE THEY LEAVE
THE EMBASSY, BUT--
AS PLANNED AND AS REHEARSED.

02:54.342 --> 02:58.846
AND OUR COUNTRY WILL,
I'M SURE, BE GRATEFUL TO YOU
IF YOU WOULD ALLOW ME.

02:58.879 --> 03:02.816
I DON'T SEE WHY YOU WOULD
REFUSE THE USE OF ANY TOOL
WHICH MIGHT AID IN THE ACC--

03:02.850 --> 03:06.086
YOU WANT TO MICROMANAGE
THE LITTLE PLAYERS,
GET A CHESSBOARD.

03:08.889 --> 03:11.425
I'M REQUIRED TO TELL YOU
THAT THERE WILL BE
A RECORD...

03:11.459 --> 03:14.228
OF THE FOOD AND BEVERAGE
CHARGES AGAINST YOUR PART
OF THE OPERATION...

03:14.262 --> 03:17.431
BOTH HERE
AND IN THE IRANIAN EMBASSY.

03:17.465 --> 03:20.868
AND THAT CONCLUDES
THIS PORTION
OF THE PRESENTATION.

03:20.901 --> 03:24.238
ALL RIGHT, GENTLEMEN,
AS REHEARSED, WHILE INSIDE
THE IRANIAN EMBASSY,

03:24.272 --> 03:27.107
YOU ARE OF COURSE
REPRESENTATIVES NOT ONLY
OF YOUR COUNTRY, BUT OF--

03:27.140 --> 03:31.044
YOU AND YOUR MEN ARE HERE
STRICTLY AS A PROTECTIVE DETAIL.
DO I HAVE THAT RIGHT?

03:31.078 --> 03:34.848
I ASSURE YOU.
OH, DON'T ASSURE ME,
SERGEANT. DON'T ASSURE ME.

03:34.882 --> 03:37.385
BECAUSE, FIRST OF ALL,
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS?

03:38.752 --> 03:40.921
YOU KEEP YOUR OWN PEOPLE
UNDER SURVEILLANCE, SIR?

03:40.954 --> 03:43.724
WOULD YOU WERE MY PEOPLE.
DO YOU SPEAK RUSSIAN?

03:43.757 --> 03:45.259
[ Speaking Foreign Language ]

03:48.396 --> 03:50.498
FARSI?

03:53.133 --> 03:55.903
GOD LOVE YOU FOR A LIAR.

03:55.936 --> 03:58.539
THE REASON I ASK--
SIR, LET ME GUARANTEE YOU--

03:58.572 --> 04:01.975
THE REASON I ASK IS
I DON'T WANT ANY OF YOU COWBOYS,
WHATEVER YOUR MISSION IS--

04:02.009 --> 04:05.579
SIR, OUR MISSION IS THE SECURITY
OF YOU AND YOUR PRINCIPALS.

04:05.613 --> 04:07.748
WHATEVER YOUR MISSION IS,

04:07.781 --> 04:11.051
TO BETRAY BY WORD OR DEED
YOUR UNDERSTANDING
OF THESE PROCEEDINGS--

04:11.084 --> 04:13.887
I ASSURE YOU.
AND SECONDLY,

04:13.921 --> 04:17.291
WHAT WE HAVE GOT HERE
IS A LONG, LONG-AWAITED
OPPORTUNITY...

04:17.325 --> 04:20.127
FOR DIPLOMACY
BETWEEN US, THE RUSSIANS
AND THE IRANIANS.

04:20.160 --> 04:22.430
DIPLOMACY,
WHICH IS DIFFERENT
TO KICKING THE DOOR DOWN.

04:22.463 --> 04:25.132
LET ME GUARANTEE YOU--
AND--

04:25.165 --> 04:29.169
AND I DO NOT TAKE IT HAPPILY
THAT YOU HAVE BEEN
SENT IN HERE...

04:29.202 --> 04:32.906
ON THE COVERT SIDE TO TEAR IT
ALL APART LIKE A BUNCH OF
MONKEYS AT A QUILTING BEE.

04:32.940 --> 04:34.942
[ Man ]
MR. CHARGE D'AFFAIRES?

04:38.145 --> 04:40.180
[ Sighs ]

04:45.319 --> 04:48.989
I-- I--
I WANT THEM TO MAKE SURE
THEY UNDERSTAND THAT.

04:52.693 --> 04:54.728
[ Man ]
BRING 'EM IN.

04:58.799 --> 05:01.702
YOU GOT A MINUTE?
SIR?

05:01.735 --> 05:04.338
ONE OF YOUR MEN'S NAME
IS BROWN?
YES, SIR.

05:04.372 --> 05:06.640
NEW MAN?
RANGERS AND AIRBORNE.

05:06.674 --> 05:09.810
AH. FIRST TIME ON PROTECTIVE?
I'D TRUST MY FAMILY
TO HIM, SIR.

05:09.843 --> 05:12.513
THIS HIS PASSPORT?

05:12.546 --> 05:15.349
IT APPEARS TO BE.
KEEP HIM OUTSIDE
THE EMBASSY.

05:15.383 --> 05:17.951
SIR?
PUT HIM OUT ON PERIMETER
OR SOMETHING.

05:17.985 --> 05:20.988
WHEN WE GO IN,
I WANT HIM OUTSIDE.
SIR,

05:21.021 --> 05:23.357
MY MISSION WITH WHICH
I AM TASKED,
AS YOU ARE WITH YOURS,

05:23.391 --> 05:25.959
REQUIRES MY ENTIRE TEAM
INSIDE THE EMBASSY.

05:25.993 --> 05:28.796
THIS MAN STAYS OUTSIDE.
MIGHT I ASK WHY, SIR?

05:28.829 --> 05:31.365
[ Sighs ]
HERE'S WHY.

05:31.399 --> 05:34.334
HE HAS MADE,
IN THE LAST THREE YEARS,

05:34.368 --> 05:37.037
- FIVE TRIPS TO ISRAEL.
- FIVE TRIPS TO ISRAEL?

05:37.070 --> 05:39.306
IS HE A JEW?
WHAT WAS HE DOING THERE?

05:39.339 --> 05:42.009
SIR, I DO NOT KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW EITHER.

05:42.042 --> 05:45.746
BUT MAYBE OUR FRIENDS
ON THE OTHER SIDE KNOW.
I'M NOT CHANCING IT.

05:45.779 --> 05:49.182
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
[ Exhales ]

05:49.216 --> 05:53.220
LOOK HERE.
YOU GUYS HAVE BEEN
FOISTED ON ME...

05:53.253 --> 05:55.989
TO SCREW UP
15 MONTHS OF DIPLOMACY.

05:56.023 --> 05:58.091
NOW, WHATEVER IT IS
YOU'RE DOING,

05:58.125 --> 06:01.562
IF YOU'RE CAUGHT,
MY CONFERENCE GOES
DOWN THE DRAIN.

06:01.595 --> 06:05.833
YOUR KID MAY BE A JEW.
HE MAY BE A SPY. HE MAY BE
BUYING RELICS OF THE HOLY LAND.

06:05.866 --> 06:09.169
BUT IF THE QUESTION OCCURRED
TO ME, IT LIKELY OCCURRED
TO THE IRANIANS.

06:09.202 --> 06:11.405
YOU WANT HIM TO DRIVE A CAR?
FINE.

06:11.439 --> 06:14.408
BUT HE IS NOT GOING
INSIDE THAT EMBASSY.

06:14.442 --> 06:16.677
SIR, IT IS MY ABSOLUTE
UNDERSTANDING--

06:16.710 --> 06:18.846
WELL, YOU HAVE
YOUR UNDERSTANDING.
I'VE GOT MY MARINES.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.914
THERE YOU HAVE IT.

06:31.559 --> 06:33.393
[ Engine Starts ]

06:35.062 --> 06:37.598
[ Engine Starts ]

06:42.903 --> 06:45.105
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

06:45.138 --> 06:47.475
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

06:47.508 --> 06:49.943
* HERE WE GO
ON THE ROAD *

06:49.977 --> 06:52.079
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

06:52.112 --> 06:54.214
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

06:54.247 --> 06:57.350
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *

07:09.530 --> 07:12.466
[ Ryan ]
WE HAD A TEAM
WENT DOWN IN THE DESERT.

07:12.500 --> 07:15.636
TWENTY-TWO MEN KILLED.
UNIT MEMBERS, JUST LIKE YOU.

07:15.669 --> 07:19.339
TWENTY-TWO MEN KILLED.
HOW'D THAT HAPPEN?

07:19.372 --> 07:21.475
SOMEBODY WITH
A ROCKET-PROPELLED GRENADE...

07:21.509 --> 07:23.911
JUST HAPPENED TO KNOW
THE POINT OF INSERTION.

07:23.944 --> 07:26.847
SHOT THE HELO DOWN.
ISN'T THAT RANDOM?

07:26.880 --> 07:29.483
HOW'D THAT HAPPEN?
HOW'D THAT HAPPEN, SOLDIER?

07:29.517 --> 07:32.285
- SIR, I DO NOT KNOW.
- WELL, WE GOT A LEAK.

07:32.319 --> 07:35.923
CHAIN OF COMMAND
OVER THERE LEAKS WORSE
THAN A BROKEN SIEVE.

07:35.956 --> 07:38.291
CAPTAIN GETS AN IDEA,
SENDS IN HIS MAN,

07:38.325 --> 07:40.528
KICKS IT UP
THE LEVEL OF COMMAND.

07:40.561 --> 07:42.930
GETS IT TO A LEVEL WHERE
SOMEBODY CAN MAKE A DECISION,

07:42.963 --> 07:45.833
THEY CALL EVERYONE
THEY KNOW TO CHAT.

07:45.866 --> 07:48.201
THOSE PEOPLE GOSSIP ABOUT IT
WITH THEIR INSIGNIFICANT OTHERS.

07:48.235 --> 07:50.337
COMMAND KICKS IT BACK DOWN
WITH THEIR IMPROVEMENTS.

07:50.370 --> 07:52.305
BY THE TIME
YOUR BROTHERS-IN-ARMS...

07:52.339 --> 07:56.143
CLIMB INTO THAT HELICOPTER,
EVERY MAN, BOY,
JACK AND MULE...

07:56.176 --> 07:59.647
IN THE TRISTATE AREA
KNOWS THE EXACT LOCATION,
TIME AND WIND DIRECTION...

07:59.680 --> 08:01.849
OF THEIR
POINT OF INSERTION.

08:01.882 --> 08:05.953
AND SOMEBODY WITH AN R.P.G.
SITTING THERE SENT 'EM
TO MEET THEIR MAKER.

08:05.986 --> 08:08.121
NOW I ASK YOU--

08:08.155 --> 08:11.525
A FELLA IN COMBAT
FALLS IN A FIREFIGHT,
THAT'S A TRAGEDY.

08:11.559 --> 08:14.695
A FELLA DIES BECAUSE SOMEBODY'S
WIFE MAKES A COMMENT
TO THE GREEN GROCER--

08:14.728 --> 08:16.664
WHAT IS THAT?

08:16.697 --> 08:19.733
SIR?
IT AIN'T A TRAGEDY.
IT'S A CRYIN' SHAME.

08:19.767 --> 08:22.135
- AND IT'S AVOIDABLE,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY, SERGEANT?
- SIR!

08:22.169 --> 08:25.438
WOULDN'T YOU SAY,
SERGEANT, THAT MEN DIE
IN COMBAT DUE TO LOOSE TALK?

08:27.107 --> 08:30.110
MRS. JOHNSON,
YOU READ THE BIBLE.

08:31.078 --> 08:33.647
COLONEL?

08:33.681 --> 08:36.049
I READ HERE IN YOUR DOSSIER
THAT YOU GO TO CHURCH.

08:36.083 --> 08:38.218
- I--
- IT'S IN THE BIBLE.

08:38.251 --> 08:40.387
GOSSIP KILLS THREE.

08:40.420 --> 08:43.523
THE ONE WHO TALKS,
THE ONE WHO LISTENS
AND THE ONE WHO'S SPOKEN OF.

08:43.557 --> 08:46.560
COLONEL, I MADE A SIMPLE REMARK.
I WAS TALKING--

08:46.594 --> 08:50.931
YOU'VE BEEN RECORDED
AS SAYING, "MY HUSBAND'S UNIT
DESIGNATION IS LOGISTICS,

08:50.964 --> 08:53.233
BUT THAT'S NOT
ACTUALLY WHAT HE DOES."
THE CONTEXT OF MY--

08:53.266 --> 08:55.502
"ACTUALLY, HE'S IN
THE COUNTERTERRORIST COMMAND."
AND?

08:55.535 --> 08:57.771
- COLONEL, I WAS TALKING--
- YES, YOU WERE,
AND TO WHAT PURPOSE...

08:57.805 --> 08:59.873
I DO NOT KNOW EXCEPT
TO CALL IT GOSSIP.

08:59.907 --> 09:03.243
AND WHILE THAT GOSSIP
DID NOT-- EXCUSE ME.
COLONEL--

09:03.276 --> 09:08.015
WHILE THAT GOSSIP DID NOT,
THAT WE KNOW, CAUSE, AS YET,
HARM TO OTHERS,

09:08.048 --> 09:10.784
IT HAS COST YOUR HUSBAND
HIS PLACE IN MY COMMAND.

09:10.818 --> 09:13.721
YOU JUST KICKED
YOUR HUSBAND OUT OF
THE UNIT, MRS. JOHNSON.

09:22.730 --> 09:24.765
HOW ABOUT THAT?

09:29.737 --> 09:33.073
[ Chattering ]
[ Shutters Clicking ]

09:33.106 --> 09:37.410
[ All Speaking Farsi ]

09:38.278 --> 09:40.948
[ Speaking Farsi ]

09:46.820 --> 09:49.456
[ Speaking Farsi ]

09:55.863 --> 09:57.765
[ Shutters Clicking ]
[ Chattering ]

10:07.007 --> 10:09.042
[ Chattering Continues ]
[ Shutters Clicking ]

10:24.057 --> 10:26.593
TAKE THE PERIMETER.
THE PERIMETER?

10:26.626 --> 10:29.462
- THEY'VE GOT THE PERIMETER.
- FLAG ON THE PLAY.
YOU'VE BEEN NIXED. SIT OUT.

10:29.496 --> 10:32.265
I'VE BEEN NIXED?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

10:32.299 --> 10:34.367
[ Whispering, Indistinct ]

10:34.401 --> 10:37.004
- WHAT?
- [ Speaking Farsi ]

10:37.037 --> 10:41.441
I'M ON THE BENCH
BECAUSE I'M A JEW?

10:41.474 --> 10:44.644
IT'S AS I SAID.
[ Speaking Farsi ]

10:54.855 --> 10:57.490
[ Speaking
Foreign Language ]

11:07.167 --> 11:09.102
[ Speaking Russian ]

11:15.943 --> 11:20.147
MY MEN HAVE ALREADY CHECKED
THE OFFICE SUITE AND CORRIDOR.

11:20.180 --> 11:24.217
EVERYTHING IS SECURE.
THE CONFERENCE ROOM?

11:31.191 --> 11:33.961
[ Speaking Farsi ]

11:48.208 --> 11:51.644
[ Continues In Farsi ]

11:59.252 --> 12:02.655
[ Speaking Farsi ]

12:10.297 --> 12:12.399
PLEASE.

12:14.001 --> 12:16.069
NOW I'M GOING
TO SHOW YOU MY OFFICE.

12:18.138 --> 12:20.007
THIS WAY, PLEASE.

12:21.441 --> 12:24.444
SCHEDULING PROBLEM.
IN SECRET.

12:24.477 --> 12:26.713
SIR, PLEASE COME THIS WAY.
THE MEETING IS ABOUT TO--
YEAH. OKAY.

12:26.746 --> 12:29.616
AGE BEFORE BEAUTY.
AGE BEFORE BEAUTY.

12:29.649 --> 12:31.618
ALL RIGHT.

12:33.620 --> 12:36.756
LET'S GET STARTED,
MR. AMBASSADOR.

12:46.666 --> 12:49.669
LET ME SHOW YOU
THE SECURITY OFFICE.

12:49.702 --> 12:51.905
CAN MY MAN GET
A CUP OF COFFEE?

12:51.939 --> 12:54.374
OF COURSE.
COME TO THE SECURITY OFFICE.

13:00.380 --> 13:02.615
[ Mrs. Johnson Sobbing ]

13:02.649 --> 13:06.453
JOHNNY-- JOHNNY--
ALL RIGHT.

13:06.486 --> 13:09.022
ALL RIGHT, I'M GONNA GO BACK.
NO--

13:09.056 --> 13:11.992
LISTEN TO ME.

13:12.025 --> 13:16.329
I AM GOING TO GO
TO PLEAD WITH HIM
TO REINSTATE YOU.

13:16.363 --> 13:18.932
THEN I'M GONNA--
[ Sobbing ]

13:18.966 --> 13:20.968
LISTEN TO ME.

13:21.001 --> 13:23.837
I AM GONNA GO TO PLEAD--

13:26.306 --> 13:28.508
GET THE IDEA?

13:28.541 --> 13:30.878
YOU KNOW WHAT YOUR
SECOND CHANCE IS, LADIES?

13:30.911 --> 13:34.147
YOU CAN SPEND THE REST OF YOUR
LIFE TO THINK ABOUT HOW YOU
RUINED YOUR HUSBAND'S CAREER.

13:34.181 --> 13:37.650
WHY IS THAT?
BECAUSE THEIR CAREER DOESN'T
MEAN NOTHIN' TO ME...

13:37.684 --> 13:40.453
COMPARED TO
THE SECURITY OF THIS UNIT.

13:40.487 --> 13:43.790
DO YOU KNOW WHO'S OUT THERE
IN THE CIVILIAN WORLD
RIGHT OFF THIS BASE?

13:43.823 --> 13:46.193
AT THE CONVENIENCE STORE,
AT THE LAUNDROMAT?

13:46.226 --> 13:49.029
DO YOU KNOW WHO YOUR
SISTER-IN-LAW TALKS TO
TO PUFF HERSELF UP...

13:49.062 --> 13:51.498
BECAUSE SHE KNOWS
ONE TOO MANY THINGS?

13:51.531 --> 13:53.466
YOU DON'T KNOW.
AND NEITHER DO I.

13:53.500 --> 13:56.870
AND WHAT WE HAVE
RIGHT HERE,
IN THE LAST YEAR--

13:56.904 --> 14:00.840
THESE ARE THE PHOTOS
OF 112 MEN FROM THE SPECIAL
FORCES COMMUNITY...

14:00.874 --> 14:03.410
WHO HAVE DIED BECAUSE
SOMEBODY KNEW THEY WERE COMING.

14:03.443 --> 14:07.514
YOU CANNOT TRUST ANYONE--
ANYONE-- OUTSIDE THIS ROOM.

14:07.547 --> 14:10.417
YOU WILL GET SOMEONE KILLED.

14:10.450 --> 14:14.687
SLEEPING ON GUARD,
DRUNK ON GUARD, CONSORTING
WITH THE ENEMY.

14:14.721 --> 14:17.824
YOU RUN YOUR MOUTHS OFF
ON THE STREET, YOU'RE
NO BETTER THAN THAT.

14:17.857 --> 14:20.493
AND I FIND OUT
THAT YOU'RE DOING IT,
I WILL RUIN YOU.

14:20.527 --> 14:23.897
- COLONEL--
- NO, I'M NOT FINISHED.

14:23.931 --> 14:27.067
THIS COVER--
THE LOGISTICAL STUDIES UNIT--
IS GETTING THIN.

14:27.100 --> 14:29.502
NOW, THIS TIME--
THIS TIME--
COLONEL,

14:29.536 --> 14:33.073
WHATEVER THAT WOMAN DID,
WHATEVER HARM THAT SHE--

14:33.106 --> 14:36.209
THIS COVER GETS ANY THINNER,
AND I WILL RIP IT OUT, AND WE
WILL START FROM SCRATCH...

14:36.243 --> 14:38.711
IN A NEW DESIGNATION
ON A NEW BASE.

14:38.745 --> 14:41.281
AND YOU CAN KISS
YOUR HOMES, YOUR SCHOOLS,
YOUR JOBS GOOD-BYE.

14:41.314 --> 14:44.084
'CAUSE I'M PACKIN'
THIS CIRCUS OUT OF HERE.

14:47.720 --> 14:51.791
I WANT THE WOMEN
OF THIS UNIT SO PARANOID...

14:51.824 --> 14:55.128
THAT YOU WILL THINK TWICE
BEFORE YOU VOLUNTEER
A "NICE DAY"...

14:55.162 --> 14:57.397
TO ANYONE
OUTSIDE THIS ROOM.

14:57.430 --> 14:59.366
IT FALLS ON YOU.
YOU DO YOUR JOB.

14:59.399 --> 15:02.002
YOU HAVE ANY QUESTION
WHAT THAT MEANS,
YOU COME TO ME.

15:10.410 --> 15:12.980
THESE MEN ARE ALL DEAD.

15:16.816 --> 15:20.420
- COLONEL--
- I DON'T HAVE TIME FOR IT.

15:22.122 --> 15:24.257
PLEASE.

15:24.291 --> 15:26.960
I'M GOING TO ORDER
SOME COFFEE FOR YOUR MAN.
MAY I SEND HIM SOME FOOD?

15:26.994 --> 15:30.097
I'M A BODY SHORT.
I DON'T WANT MY MAN
WITH HIS HANDS FULL.

15:30.130 --> 15:32.865
[ Chattering ]

15:35.602 --> 15:38.338
WELL, WISE PRECAUTION,
BUT PERHAPS IN THIS CASE
UNNECESSARY. FAHEED--

15:38.371 --> 15:41.308
AND WHAT PRECAUTION HAVE
WE EVER FOUND UNNECESSARY?

15:41.341 --> 15:46.013
WHICH IS WHY WE TWO
OLD SOLDIERS MAY BE FATED
TO DIE IN BED.

15:46.046 --> 15:49.349
NOW WOULDN'T THAT BE
A HELL OF A THING?
CIGAR?

15:49.382 --> 15:52.285
NO, THANK YOU.
WHAT'S PERMITTED TO OTHERS
IS NOT PERMITTED TO YOU?

15:52.319 --> 15:55.088
THE INJUNCTION
OF THE ROMAN LEGIONNAIRES.

15:55.122 --> 15:57.690
AH, I SEE.

15:57.724 --> 16:00.360
I FOUND A FELLOW SCHOLAR.

16:00.393 --> 16:03.696
NO. JUST ANOTHER
OLD SOLDIER.

16:03.730 --> 16:06.199
WELL, IT'S BETTER
THAN CIVILIAN LIFE.

16:06.233 --> 16:09.369
AS WHAT IS NOT?

16:09.402 --> 16:11.371
HOW DID YOU HURT
YOUR HAND?

16:11.404 --> 16:13.306
I WAS DOING MY NAILS.
THE FILE SLIPPED.

16:17.044 --> 16:19.846
[ Phone Rings ]

16:22.682 --> 16:26.353
- [ Ringing Continues ]
- [ Beeping ]

16:26.386 --> 16:28.521
[ Rings ]

16:35.728 --> 16:38.131
[ Door Unlocks ]

16:38.165 --> 16:40.533
FORT GRIFFITH?
COMING ON NOW.

16:43.103 --> 16:45.338
[ Electronic Beeping ]

16:46.506 --> 16:49.776
ITEM BRAVO X-RAY DELTA.

16:52.912 --> 16:55.815
BRAVO X-RAY DELTA,
THIS IS ZULU...

16:55.848 --> 16:58.051
BRAVO KIOTO FOX.
WHO'S GOT IT?

16:58.085 --> 17:00.487
C.I.A. STATION CHIEF IN TEHRAN.
ITEM BRAVO.

17:00.520 --> 17:02.555
ITEM BRAVO,
YOU HAVE MY ATTENTION.

17:02.589 --> 17:06.559
THEY ARE ZULU BRAVO.
ZULU BRAVO, WE HAVE
YOUR MAN INSIDE THE EMBASSY.

17:06.593 --> 17:09.362
HE WILL NOT--
I REPEAT, NOT RESPOND
TO MY REQUEST FOR UPDATE.

17:09.396 --> 17:12.365
- ARE YOU REPORTING
FAILURE OF THE MISSION?
- [ Static ]

17:12.399 --> 17:14.734
- ARE-- ARE YOU REPORTING
FAILURE OF THE MISSION?
- NO, SIR.

17:14.767 --> 17:18.004
NO, SIR, I AM NOT
REPORTING YOUR FAILURE
OF THE MISSION.

17:18.037 --> 17:21.007
HE-- HE IS INSIDE
THE EMBASSY AND POISED
FOR THE PASS.

17:21.040 --> 17:23.876
THE DIPLOMATIC SIDE
PULLED PART--
[ Static ]

17:23.910 --> 17:27.580
- PULLED PART OF HIS TEAM
OFF THE MISSION.
- WHY IS THAT?

17:27.614 --> 17:31.884
BECAUSE THE MAN'S A JEW.
I BELIEVE HE FEARED
IT MIGHT OFFEND THE IRANIANS.

17:31.918 --> 17:34.087
THEY DID WHAT?
[ Static ]

17:34.121 --> 17:36.523
WHO'S OUR MAN
IN THE FOREIGN SERVICE?
GET HIM ON THE LINE.

17:36.556 --> 17:38.691
THIS TRANSMISSION
BREAKS IN 25 SECONDS.

17:38.725 --> 17:41.394
ALL RIGHT.
TELL ME AGAIN.

17:41.428 --> 17:44.531
YOU'RE WHINING TO ME
AFTER MY TEAM WAS GUTTED
BECAUSE MY MAN'S A JEW?

17:44.564 --> 17:47.600
WELL, HE'S GOT FIVE ISRAELI
STAMPS ON HIS PASSPORT.

17:47.634 --> 17:51.271
THAT'S SOME KIND OF MISTAKE.
NO. NO, I'M LOOKING
AT HIS PASSPORT RIGHT HERE.

17:51.304 --> 17:53.273
NUMBER--
SO THE MISSION'S FAILED?

17:53.306 --> 17:55.942
ITEM BRAVO X-RAY DELTA--
NO, SIR.
THE AGENT IN PLACE...

17:55.975 --> 17:57.977
IS A CIVILIAN EMPLOYEE
OF THE IRANIANS.

17:58.010 --> 18:00.647
THE WOMAN IS NOT DUE
TO EXIT THE EMBASSY
FOR ANOTHER--

18:00.680 --> 18:03.416
HANG ON.
GET ME OUT OF HERE.
THEY STILL--

18:03.450 --> 18:05.618
THEY STILL--

18:05.652 --> 18:08.488
THEY STILL HAVE
THE 10 MINUTES.

18:08.521 --> 18:11.924
WE STILL HAVE THE--

18:11.958 --> 18:14.994
HELLO? HELLO? I--
[ Crackling ]

18:15.027 --> 18:18.097
ITEM BRAVO?
[ Crackling ]

18:18.131 --> 18:20.300
ITEM BRAVO, WE ARE
LOSING THE CARRIER WAVE.

18:20.333 --> 18:23.603
[ Crackling Continues ]
WE'RE LOSING THE SIGNAL.

18:23.636 --> 18:25.972
IS THAT WHAT WE'RE DOING?

18:28.608 --> 18:30.643
I'M SORRY.
I NEED TO BUY WHAT?

18:30.677 --> 18:33.079
SUPPLIES
FOR THE F.R.G. MEETING.

18:33.112 --> 18:35.248
LIFE GOES ON.

18:35.282 --> 18:38.351
AND ARMY LIFE
IN THE F.R.G. IS RUN ON
POSTER BOARD AND COOKIES.

18:38.385 --> 18:41.588
SO IF YOU GET
THE POSTER BOARD, I'LL SEE
YOU AT THE MEETING TONIGHT.

18:41.621 --> 18:44.090
YOU DIDN'T THINK THAT WAS
A LITTLE EXCESSIVE, MOLLY?

18:44.123 --> 18:46.626
I AM NEITHER BLIND
NOR INSENSITIVE.

18:46.659 --> 18:48.961
WHY WAS HE SO BRUTAL?

18:48.995 --> 18:51.964
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT WE ARE.
WE ARE AT WAR.

18:51.998 --> 18:54.967
AND THE MORE WE SWEAT
IN TRAINING, THE LESS
WE BLEED IN COMBAT.

18:55.001 --> 18:58.205
AND THAT IS THE SAD,
UNFORTUNATE TRUTH.

18:58.238 --> 19:00.173
COLONEL?

19:00.207 --> 19:02.975
I'LL SEE YOU
AT THE MEETING TONIGHT.

19:03.009 --> 19:07.380
COLONEL, YOU'RE A ROUGH
OLD SOLDIER WITH A ROUGH OLD
SOLDIER'S WAY, IS THAT IT?

19:07.414 --> 19:10.183
YOU HAVE ISSUE WITH
MY COMMAND STYLE, MS. BLANE?

19:10.217 --> 19:13.386
MS. SERGEANT BLANE?
THAT AIN'T THE ISSUE.

19:13.420 --> 19:15.455
YOU JUST SCARED
MY NEWBIE WIFE TO DEATH.

19:15.488 --> 19:18.225
ARE YOU UNAWARE
OF THAT, COLONEL?

19:18.258 --> 19:21.994
OLD FRIEND, I JUST TOSSED
ONE OF 130 TRIGGER PULLERS...

19:22.028 --> 19:25.265
IN A UNIT THAT I REQUIRE
A MINIMUM OF THREE TIMES
THAT NUMBER.

19:28.268 --> 19:31.003
I WAS A LITTLE BLUNT.

19:31.037 --> 19:33.573
DOES THAT SET YOUR METER
BACK TO ZERO?

19:33.606 --> 19:36.008
EXCUSE ME.

19:39.412 --> 19:42.582
I'VE GOTTA TALK TO YOU.
I'VE GOTTA TALK TO YOU
RIGHT NOW.

19:42.615 --> 19:46.253
YEAH.
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.
IT'S OVER.

19:46.286 --> 19:49.188
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?
- THAT'S WHAT I MEAN.

19:53.460 --> 19:56.596
I'M SORRY, SIR.
NO, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
UH--

19:58.030 --> 20:00.700
I MEAN, THE NEED FOR SECURITY
TRUMPS THE BOARD.

20:00.733 --> 20:05.872
AND THAT MAY BE HARSH, BUT--
AND I'M SORRY
IF THAT'S HARSH, BUT, UH,

20:05.905 --> 20:08.074
I DON'T KNOW ANOTHER WAY.

20:08.107 --> 20:10.243
COULD YOU HAVE SOMEBODY CLEAN
THAT WINDOW, PLEASE,

20:10.277 --> 20:12.612
AND GET THOSE
FINGERPRINTS OFF THERE?
OKAY.

20:14.481 --> 20:18.017
[ Sighs ]
3:00, THE PLACE.

20:18.050 --> 20:20.287
WE'LL TALK.
I DON'T THINK SO.

20:20.320 --> 20:22.755
COLONEL, I'M NOT SURE
I UNDERSTAND YOU.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.427
I NEED YOU.

20:47.647 --> 20:51.217
SUBJECT'S BEEN INSIDE
45 MINUTES. I DO NOT KNOW
IF THE PASS HAS BEEN MADE YET.

20:51.250 --> 20:53.252
THANK YOU.

20:57.256 --> 21:00.693
[ Speaking Farsi ]

21:12.705 --> 21:15.041
[ Speaks Farsi ]

21:19.879 --> 21:22.482
- WE STARTED TO FIGHT.
- WELL, I BETTER GO CHECK--

21:22.515 --> 21:25.352
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO.
PLEASE STAY.
THEY WILL CALL US...

21:25.385 --> 21:27.520
SHOULD THE MONGOL HORDES
BREACH OUR DEFENSES.

21:27.554 --> 21:29.522
WELL, YOU KNOW, IF I'M NOT
LOOKING AT THE TROOPS,

21:29.556 --> 21:32.859
THEY'RE APT TO FALL
INTO UNFORTUNATE HABITS.

21:32.892 --> 21:35.928
SWAPPING KNIVES,
SHOWING EACH OTHER
THEIR WAR WOUNDS AND ALL.

21:35.962 --> 21:39.165
- YOUR TROOPS IN THIS INSTANCE
IS ONE MAN--
- AND A MAN OUTSIDE.

21:39.198 --> 21:42.101
OH, YES.
AND YOUR MAN EXILED OUTSIDE.

21:42.134 --> 21:45.171
WE WERE TALKING
ABOUT THE DESERT.
WHEN WE WERE IN IRAQ,

21:45.204 --> 21:49.275
THE SOLDIERS WERE
LAYING DOWN, HUNGRY.

21:49.308 --> 21:52.311
BUT WE COULDN'T DO ANYTHING
BECAUSE OUR SOLDIERS
WERE HUNGRY TOO.

21:52.345 --> 21:55.548
[ Speaking Farsi ]

22:02.922 --> 22:07.326
IT WAS YOUR PEOPLE WHO SAID
YOU COULD NOT BE ADMITTED.
YOUR PEOPLE.

22:07.360 --> 22:10.830
SIMPLE OPERATIONAL CHANGE.
NO, THEY DISCOVERED
YOUR RELIGION...

22:10.863 --> 22:14.501
AND FEARED THAT YOUR
PRESENCE MIGHT OFFEND US.

22:14.534 --> 22:16.736
COULD IT BE MORE SHAMEFUL?
I DON'T THINK SO.

22:18.605 --> 22:23.309
THE HIGHEST GOOD
IS HOSPITALITY.

22:23.342 --> 22:26.212
[ Bob ]
IS IT NORMAL FOR YOUR GARAGE
TO BE UNLOCKED?

22:26.245 --> 22:29.215
AND HIGHER THAN HOSPITALITY
IS SECURITY.

22:32.552 --> 22:34.353
SORRY.

22:40.292 --> 22:42.962
[ Man Shouts in Farsi ]

22:45.131 --> 22:47.467
[ Man ]
COME ON! COME ON!

22:54.073 --> 22:56.409
[ Men Speaking Farsi ]

22:58.611 --> 23:00.480
[ Speaking Farsi ]

23:06.586 --> 23:08.455
[ Man Speaking Farsi ]

23:25.472 --> 23:27.507
[ Car Door Slams ]

23:30.309 --> 23:33.245
* [ Country ]

23:33.279 --> 23:35.582
HELLO?

23:35.615 --> 23:38.551
HELP YOU?
I CALLED
ABOUT THE POSTER BOARD?

23:38.585 --> 23:40.787
YES, MA'AM.
JUST GOT IT IN.

23:40.820 --> 23:44.223
POSTER BOARD, BANNERS, SO ON.
WE CAN'T KEEP 'EM IN STOCK.

23:44.256 --> 23:49.095
"WELCOME HOME." "GOOD LUCK."
WHAT KIND OF POSTER YOU NEEDING?

23:49.128 --> 23:53.165
"FAMILY READINESS GROUP."
"FAMILY READINESS GROUP."

23:53.199 --> 23:55.167
LONG WAY TO COME
FROM FORT GRIFFITH.

23:55.201 --> 23:57.336
BUT A LOT OF THEM DO.

23:57.369 --> 24:00.339
COME OUT HERE.
MIDDLE OF NOWHERE.

24:00.372 --> 24:02.942
NAH, BUT WE APPRECIATE
YOUR BUSINESS.

24:02.975 --> 24:05.177
YOUR HUSBAND DEPLOYED?

24:05.211 --> 24:07.647
NO.
HE'S A CLERK ON BASE.

24:07.680 --> 24:09.949
- [ Sighs ]
YEAH.
- I NEED--

24:09.982 --> 24:12.585
WHAT?
I SAID,
WHAT I REQUIRE IS--

24:12.619 --> 24:17.356
NO, I PUT THE STUFF ASIDE.
THE STUFF YOU CALLED FOR,
I PUT IT ASIDE.

24:18.825 --> 24:20.727
YEP. NOTHING IN THERE.

24:22.361 --> 24:24.363
TIFFY?

24:38.811 --> 24:40.880
TIFFY!

25:05.204 --> 25:07.373
I-- I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SAY.
HERE'S THE THING.

25:07.406 --> 25:09.809
AND LISTEN TO ME.
NO. YOU LISTEN TO ME, TIFFY.
IT'S OVER.

25:09.842 --> 25:12.044
DON'T SAY THAT.
IT'S OVER.

25:12.078 --> 25:15.214
- THEN WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?
- I CAME HERE TO TELL YOU.

25:15.247 --> 25:18.685
NO, YOU CAME HERE BECAUSE
I ASKED YOU TO COME HERE,
AND SO YOU CAME HERE FOR ME.

25:18.718 --> 25:22.054
- THAT'S OVER.
- WAIT A SECOND FOR ME
TO TELL YOU WHAT YOU NEED.

25:22.088 --> 25:25.057
I DON'T NEED YOU
TO TELL ME WHAT I NEED.
I NEED IT TO BE DONE!

25:25.091 --> 25:27.059
WHAT WAS I LECTURING ABOUT
THAT WOMAN TODAY...

25:27.093 --> 25:29.896
IF NOT SECURITY?
THIS HAS GOT NOTHING
TO DO WITH SECURITY.

25:29.929 --> 25:32.364
THEN WHAT THE HELL
DOES IT HAVE TO DO WITH THEN?

25:32.398 --> 25:35.167
WHAT DOES IT HAVE TO DO--
IT HAS TO DO WITH GUILT.

25:35.201 --> 25:37.870
YOU'RE CRAZY. YOU KNOW THAT?
YOU'RE CR-- I'M CRAZY TOO.

25:37.904 --> 25:40.072
LISTEN TO ME.

25:40.106 --> 25:43.075
YOU WANT TO CALL IT OFF,
CALL IT OFF.

25:43.109 --> 25:46.078
WE'RE CRAZY.
YEAH. SURE.

25:46.112 --> 25:50.416
BUT DON'T-- DON'T TELL ME
IT'S SECURITY.

25:50.449 --> 25:53.886
BECAUSE IF YOU WANT
TO GO OFF THE RESERVATION,
AND EVIDENCE IS YOU DO,

25:53.920 --> 25:57.790
THEN-- THEN-- THEN WHO IS IT
BEST TO DO IT WITH?

26:00.593 --> 26:03.095
HAVEN'T WE ALWAYS BEEN SAFE?

26:03.129 --> 26:06.132
HMM?

26:06.165 --> 26:08.067
IT'S GUILT, COLONEL.

26:09.568 --> 26:12.104
IT'S GUILT.

26:12.138 --> 26:14.273
AND HERE'S AN UPDATE.

26:14.306 --> 26:16.676
- YOU LIKE IT.
- NO.

26:18.945 --> 26:22.649
NO. THAT'S RIGHT.
YOU LOVE IT.

26:26.352 --> 26:28.520
I DON'T HAVE TO TELL YOU
WHAT YOU NEED.

26:29.756 --> 26:31.624
[ Sighs ]

26:36.595 --> 26:39.799
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU
GET OUT OF ME?

26:39.832 --> 26:44.336
I GET A MAN WHO LOVES ME
MORE THAN HIS DAMNED HOBBY.

26:48.274 --> 26:50.677
YOU TELL ME
THAT MAKES ME A TRAMP.

27:07.694 --> 27:09.662
[ Ryan ]
YOU COME INTO A ROOM.

27:09.696 --> 27:12.932
THERE'S A DEAD BODY
BLED OUT ON THE FLOOR.

27:12.965 --> 27:16.368
THERE'S A FELLA
STANDING OVER IT
WITH A KNIFE.

27:16.402 --> 27:18.971
IS HE A MURDERER,
OR IS HE A DOCTOR,

27:19.005 --> 27:23.342
SOME SAMARITAN TRYING
TO CUT THE CLOTHES OFF
TO GET AT THE WOUND?

27:23.375 --> 27:26.045
NOTHING IS WITHOUT A PRICE.

27:26.078 --> 27:28.647
WHAT'S THE PRICE OF SECURITY?
YOU TELL ME.

27:28.681 --> 27:30.683
SUSPICION.

27:30.717 --> 27:33.720
THAT'S CORRECT.
IT'S A TERRIBLE PRICE.

27:33.753 --> 27:36.188
DID YOU SEE THE PERSON
TIFFY MET AT THIS MOTEL?

27:37.356 --> 27:39.992
- NO, SIR.
- WAS IT A MAN OR A WOMAN?

27:40.026 --> 27:42.594
I DON'T KNOW.

27:43.595 --> 27:46.833
ALL RIGHT.
[ Sighs ]

27:48.667 --> 27:52.038
YOU SAT IN THIS CHAIR,
WHAT WOULD YOU TELL ME?

27:52.071 --> 27:54.173
GO ON.

27:56.008 --> 27:58.410
I'D TELL YOU--

27:58.444 --> 28:00.980
I'M LISTENING.

28:01.013 --> 28:03.883
NOT TO FRET.

28:03.916 --> 28:07.419
YES? BECAUSE?

28:07.453 --> 28:09.255
WE KNOW
THE WOMAN'S CHARACTER.

28:09.288 --> 28:11.791
AND?
AND--

28:14.093 --> 28:16.362
THAT YOU'D TAKE CARE OF IT.

28:16.395 --> 28:19.531
CONSIDER YOURSELF TOLD.

28:21.533 --> 28:24.703
MRS. BROWN.
THANK YOU, COLONEL.

28:36.783 --> 28:39.718
[ U.S. Ambassador ] IN SHORT,
AND FINALLY, IN THE INTERESTS
OF BOTH THE IRANIAN...

28:39.752 --> 28:41.687
AND THE RUSSIAN PEOPLES--
[ Speaking Russian ]

28:41.720 --> 28:46.058
THE INTERESTS OF ALL
THE PEACE-LOVING PEOPLE OF THE
WORLD ARE OF COURSE IDENTICAL.

28:46.092 --> 28:50.462
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Speaking Russian ]

28:50.496 --> 28:52.631
BUT SPECIFICALLY,
IN THE MATTER OF THE REACTOR--

28:52.664 --> 28:55.868
- [ Speaking Russian ]
- WE GIVE YOU OUR ASSURANCES--

28:55.902 --> 29:01.307
[ Speaking Russian ]
THAT WE WILL IMPLEMENT
THEM TO YOUR SATISFACTION.

29:01.340 --> 29:04.476
UH-HUH.

29:04.510 --> 29:09.215
[ Man ] ESPECIALLY MUST--
DON'T YOU AGREE BE BASED
UPON THE ANCIENT WAYS?

29:09.248 --> 29:12.651
BUT I RECOGNIZE--
I RECOGNIZE THE MEN
WHO TRAINED ME.

29:12.684 --> 29:15.721
THE MEN WHO TRAINED ME
HAD BEEN TRAINED BY
THOSE WHO FOUGHT--

29:15.754 --> 29:17.656
OR MAY HAVE FOUGHT--

29:17.689 --> 29:20.426
WITH T.E. LAWRENCE.
[ Phone Rings ]

29:20.459 --> 29:23.129
EXCUSE ME.

29:23.162 --> 29:27.266
[ Speaking Farsi ]

29:34.874 --> 29:37.676
[ Man Continues In Farsi ]
[ Phone Beeps ]

29:39.711 --> 29:42.414
[ Beeps ]
YES?

29:42.448 --> 29:45.117
SHIRIN?

29:47.653 --> 29:49.922
SHE'S LEAVING.
CAN'T TALK NOW.
I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

29:49.956 --> 29:51.891
[ Speaking Farsi ]

30:00.132 --> 30:04.536
MY MAN AND THE RUSSIAN
ARE TAKING A DRIVE
AFTER THE CONFERENCE,

30:04.570 --> 30:06.505
SHOULD THERE BE WATER
IN THE CAR.

30:08.507 --> 30:12.945
THEIR KNOWLEDGE OF THE DESERT
MUST BE BASED UPON
THE ANCIENT WAYS...

30:12.979 --> 30:15.982
INHERITED FROM THE PRIMITIVE,
DON'T YOU AGREE?

30:16.015 --> 30:18.150
SHE'S COMING OUT.

30:18.184 --> 30:21.720
I-- I DON'T-- I DON'T KNOW--
I DON'T KNOW IF THE PASS
HAS BEEN MADE.

30:21.753 --> 30:26.225
SHE IS RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.
SHE IS 20 FEET IN FRONT OF ME.
SHE'S CROSSING--

30:26.258 --> 30:28.660
[ Man ]
THE PROBLEM WITH HASSAN--
WE COULDN'T MOVE,

30:28.694 --> 30:31.063
AND UNFORTUNATELY
WE DID NOT HAVE ANYBODY.

30:36.502 --> 30:40.239
[ Speaking Farsi ]

31:04.730 --> 31:08.500
- SHE'S GETTING ON A BUS.
- THE GIRL LEFT THE BUILDING.

31:08.534 --> 31:11.237
THANK YOU.

31:21.247 --> 31:23.715
[ Beeping ]

31:26.652 --> 31:28.787
[ Beeping ]

31:31.223 --> 31:34.593
THEY ARE READY TO LEAVE
IN TWO MINUTES.
SHALL WE LEAVE?

31:36.462 --> 31:38.597
PLEASE.

31:40.632 --> 31:43.169
[ Men Chattering
In Foreign Language ]

31:56.482 --> 32:00.086
[ Speaking Russian ]

32:00.119 --> 32:03.089
THAT'S ABSOLUTELY NO PROBLEM.
I'LL GET A REPORT THE MOMENT--

32:03.122 --> 32:04.991
HERE THEY COME.

32:09.328 --> 32:13.199
- [ Speaking Farsi ]
- SIR?

32:15.267 --> 32:17.503
SIR?

32:21.540 --> 32:24.643
[ Whispering ]
UH, I THINK YOU SHOULD CHECK
THE FRONT TIRE OF THE CAR.

32:53.639 --> 32:57.476
WELL, MY FRIEND,
YOU DID ME A VERY GOOD TURN.

32:57.509 --> 33:00.946
[ Door Closes ]
I WOULD HAVE DELAYED
MY PRINCIPAL'S TRIP...

33:00.979 --> 33:03.282
- AND BEEN PROVEN A FOOL.
- [ Door Closes ]

33:03.315 --> 33:05.284
I FOUND WHAT WAS
TRANSMITTING.

33:05.317 --> 33:09.321
IT'S MINE. YOU SAVED ME
A GREAT DEAL OF EMBARRASSMENT.

33:09.355 --> 33:11.290
I RECEIVED A GOOD TURN
FROM MY COUSIN--
[ Phone Beeps ]

33:11.323 --> 33:14.460
THE JEW.

33:14.493 --> 33:17.696
- LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.
- AFFIRMATIVE.

33:19.031 --> 33:20.932
WAIT.

33:24.002 --> 33:26.338
FROM ONE SOLDIER
TO ANOTHER.

33:33.245 --> 33:35.947
[ Speaking Russian ]

33:38.184 --> 33:41.487
GOOD-BYE, MY FRIEND.
I TRUST WE KEPT YOU
OCCUPIED.

33:41.520 --> 33:45.491
IT WAS HARD TO DISTRACT
AN OLD WARRIOR,

33:45.524 --> 33:47.726
BUT I SUCCEEDED.

33:47.759 --> 33:53.031
I ENJOYED OUR TIME TOGETHER.
SOMETIMES YOU WIN,
SOMETIMES YOU LOSE.

33:55.101 --> 33:59.105
[ Whispering ]
RIGHT. OKAY.

33:59.138 --> 34:03.008
WAS YOUR MISSION ACCOMPLISHED?
STAY AWAY FROM ME, SON.
I WILL PUT YOU IN THE DIRT.

34:03.041 --> 34:06.112
[ Door Closes ]
[ Engine Starts ]

34:12.451 --> 34:14.586
[ Engine Starts ]

34:26.632 --> 34:28.600
[ Molly ]
WELL?

34:28.634 --> 34:30.802
DO YOU DOUBT ME?
NO, BUT--

34:30.836 --> 34:33.605
BUT?
I THINK WE NEED TO ALLOW FOR
ALTERNATIVE EXPLANATIONS.

34:33.639 --> 34:35.774
THAT'S WHAT
THE COLONEL SAID.
[ Chattering ]

34:35.807 --> 34:39.745
WAIT. YOU WENT
TO THE COLONEL?

34:41.313 --> 34:43.982
[ Chattering ]
[ Laughing ]

34:45.284 --> 34:47.953
SORRY I'M LATE.

34:47.986 --> 34:50.622
EXCUSE ME.
[ Chattering Continues ]

34:50.656 --> 34:55.727
WELL, WHAT KEPT YOU
FROM YOUR MOST FAVORITE
READINESS GROUP?

34:55.761 --> 34:59.998
WELL, I, UM-- [ Chuckles ]
I HAD TO MAKE A COUPLE
PHONE CALLS.

35:01.467 --> 35:03.635
YOU WERE SHACKED UP
IN A MOTEL
IS WHERE YOU WERE.

35:03.669 --> 35:06.672
AND OUR PRETTY
LITTLE GIRL SAW IT.

35:06.705 --> 35:10.442
THAT'S RIGHT.
AND SHE WANTS TO KNOW IF,

35:10.476 --> 35:12.578
THINKING THAT SHE'S DISCOV--
DOES SHE--

35:12.611 --> 35:15.247
HAS DISCOVERED
YOUR INDISCRETION--

35:15.281 --> 35:17.683
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

35:17.716 --> 35:20.452
DOES SHE KNOW
WHO I WAS THERE WITH?

35:20.486 --> 35:22.488
WAS IT HER DUTY
TO GO TO THE COLONEL?

35:22.521 --> 35:24.956
AND SHE WENT TO THE COLONEL.

35:24.990 --> 35:28.594
- [ Laughing ]
- [ Chuckles ]
HELP ME, MOLLY--

35:28.627 --> 35:31.263
YOU SWORE TO ME.

35:31.297 --> 35:34.666
WEEPING, YOU SWORE
THAT IT WAS OVER.

35:34.700 --> 35:36.868
NOW TELL ME A LIE.

35:36.902 --> 35:39.205
I, UM--

35:39.238 --> 35:44.810
IF YOUR HUSBAND FINDS OUT,
DO YOU KNOW WHAT
HE'S BOUND TO DO?

35:44.843 --> 35:49.381
I--
NOW TELL ME, HOW DOES IT
END IN SOME GUNFIRE?

35:49.415 --> 35:54.553
I SWEAR ON MY LIFE--
MOLLY, ON MY LIFE,
I WILL NEVER SEE HIM AGAIN.

35:56.888 --> 36:00.692
I WISH I WAS SMARTER.
I SWEAR TO THE LORD I DO.

36:06.332 --> 36:08.867
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

36:08.900 --> 36:12.103
THEY SEEM TO HAVE FAILED.
THEY DIDN'T MAKE THE PASS.

36:13.905 --> 36:16.842
WE'RE AWAITING THE RETURN
OF THE TEAM.

36:16.875 --> 36:19.311
THEY'RE HERE.
[ Electronic Beeping ]

36:19.345 --> 36:21.447
THEY'RE HERE.

36:25.584 --> 36:27.753
[ Chattering ]

36:31.557 --> 36:34.860
[ Mutters, Indistinct ]
THANK YOU.

36:34.893 --> 36:36.895
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU, GENTLEMEN.
THANK YOU.

36:36.928 --> 36:38.930
LONG MORNING.
THANK YOU ALL.

36:38.964 --> 36:40.999
[ Man ]
THIS FACILITY IS NOW
AT CONDITION THREE.

36:41.032 --> 36:43.201
WHICH WAY ARE THE RUSSIANS
GONNA JUMP?

36:43.235 --> 36:45.771
THAT'S WHAT WASHINGTON
IS GOING TO ASK.
WHAT AM I GONNA TELL THEM?

36:45.804 --> 36:48.039
CAN WE GET SOME FOOD
UPSTAIRS, PLEASE?

36:48.073 --> 36:50.376
SIR, THERE'S A 5:00 P.M.
MEETING IN THE STAFF ROOM.

36:53.879 --> 36:55.847
[ Woman's Voice ]
ALL EMBASSY EMPLOYEES,

36:55.881 --> 36:58.884
THIS FACILITY IS NOW
IN CONDITION THREE.

36:58.917 --> 37:00.886
THE FACILITY IS NOW
IN CONDITION--

37:07.626 --> 37:10.462
I CAN USE A CUP OF COFFEE.

37:10.496 --> 37:12.964
WHO DO I HAVE TO SHOOT...

37:12.998 --> 37:14.900
TO GET A CUP OF COFFEE?

37:18.637 --> 37:22.240
I WOULD LIKE YOUR CREW
OUT OF HERE TONIGHT.

37:22.274 --> 37:25.577
YES, SIR.
OH, AND, UH,

37:25.611 --> 37:29.481
THIS IS YOUR BILL FOR YOUR
FOOD AND DRINK WHILE
YOU WERE AT THE EMBASSY.

37:29.515 --> 37:33.319
THAT'S NOT VERY HOSPITABLE.
NOT VERY HOSPITABLE AT ALL.
WHAT'S THAT?

37:35.454 --> 37:37.756
SIR, IT IS A--
I BELIEVE A YATAGHAN,

37:37.789 --> 37:41.493
- A CEREMONIAL MUSLIM DAGGER.
- PASS IT HERE, PLEASE.

37:41.527 --> 37:44.563
IT WAS A GIFT.

37:44.596 --> 37:47.799
ALL GIFTS OR MEMENTOS
RECEIVED DURING THE PERFORMANCE
OF EMBASSY DUTIES...

37:47.833 --> 37:51.269
ARE THE PROPERTY
OF THE UNITED STATES.
IT WAS A GIFT OF FRIENDSHIP.

37:51.303 --> 37:54.205
PERHAPS YOU SHOULD GIVE
MORE THOUGHT TO ALLEGIANCE,
SOLDIER.

37:58.310 --> 38:00.679
SIR?

38:00.712 --> 38:03.214
IF I CAN HAVE ONE MOMENT
OF YOUR TIME.

38:07.319 --> 38:10.956
THANK YOU FOR YOUR HOSPITALITY.
YOU MAY KEEP THE CHANGE.

38:17.463 --> 38:20.599
PERHAPS YOU SHOULD HAVE
ACCEPTED MY HELP.

38:20.632 --> 38:22.901
CODE ROOM, FIVE MINUTES.

38:28.507 --> 38:30.976
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.
[ Laughing ]

38:31.009 --> 38:33.979
WHAT I AM ABOUT TO REVEAL
TO YOU I SHOULD NOT BE
TELLING YOU,

38:34.012 --> 38:37.783
AND I ONLY DO SO
AS IT IS ESSENTIAL TO
OUR UNIT'S SECURITY.

38:37.816 --> 38:41.787
WHAT YOU SAW WAS--
WHAT YOU SAW
WAS WHAT I THOUGHT.

38:41.820 --> 38:44.456
TIFFANY RECEIVED A CALL--
THIS HAS TO STAY BETWEEN US.

38:44.490 --> 38:46.658
THERE IS A WOMAN--

38:46.692 --> 38:52.030
NO, NOT IN THE UNIT--
ON THE BASE
WHO IS BEING ABUSED.

38:52.063 --> 38:54.232
SHE'S NOT HERE NOW.

38:54.265 --> 38:57.736
THIS WOMAN HAS TRIED
SEVERAL TIMES TO ESCAPE
THAT MARRIAGE.

38:57.769 --> 39:00.205
SHE WAS BEATEN, AND SHE--
FROM THE MOTEL,

39:00.238 --> 39:04.042
SHE CALLED TIFFANY FOR AID.

39:04.075 --> 39:06.077
[ Women Laughing ]

39:06.111 --> 39:08.046
[ Sighs ]
OH, THANK GOD.

39:11.082 --> 39:15.086
THANK YOU, MOLLY.
THANK YOU.

39:15.120 --> 39:17.022
YOU DID RIGHT, GIRL.

39:19.124 --> 39:21.092
[ Exhales ]

39:21.126 --> 39:23.529
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

39:23.562 --> 39:25.731
[ Woman ]
EXCELLENT.

39:25.764 --> 39:28.333
- [ Electronic Beeping ]
- STAND BY FOR WASHINGTON.

39:28.366 --> 39:30.936
[ Radio Static ]

39:30.969 --> 39:33.271
YOU READY TO TAKE
YOUR BEATING?

39:33.304 --> 39:36.942
SIR, WE REPORT FAILURE TO--
FAILURE TO PLANT THE DEVICE.

39:36.975 --> 39:39.578
GIVE ME THE BOX.

39:39.611 --> 39:44.182
THE MAN WE WERE ASSIGNED
WAS UNABLE TO PASS THE DEVICE
TO THE AGENT IN PLACE, AND SO--

39:44.215 --> 39:48.086
WELL, YES, SIR.
THAT IS, I MOST HEARTILY
REGRET TO SO INFORM YOU.

39:48.119 --> 39:51.356
NO, WE OFFERED THEM
OUR ASSISTANCE, SIR.

39:51.389 --> 39:54.025
IS THAT A FAIR ASSESSMENT?

39:54.059 --> 39:56.762
IS THAT A FAIR ASSESSMENT,
SERGEANT? HOLDING.

40:00.331 --> 40:03.469
ALL RIGHT.
THE BOX IS EMPTY.

40:03.502 --> 40:06.404
WHERE'S THE DEVICE?
WHERE IS THE DEVICE,
YOUNG SERGEANT?

40:06.438 --> 40:09.374
SERGEANT MAJOR?
THE LISTENING DEVICE.
WHERE IS IT?

40:09.407 --> 40:12.778
SERGEANT MAJOR, IT IS BEHIND
THE CUSHION OF THE IRANIAN
AMBASSADOR'S LIMOUSINE,

40:12.811 --> 40:15.814
EXACTLY WHERE I PUT IT.
AND WHAT IS IT DOING
THERE, LAD?

40:15.847 --> 40:19.150
SERGEANT MAJOR, AS IT IS
A TRANSMITTING DEVICE, IT IS
MOST LIKELY TRANSMITTING.

40:19.184 --> 40:23.655
- [ Jonas ] AND THE FREQUENCY?
- TWO-FOUR-FIVE
ON THE "B" SIDE VAN.

40:23.689 --> 40:26.157
[ Radio Static ]

40:26.191 --> 40:29.327
[ Man ] WASHINGTON
BACK ON THE LINE.
SIR, CAN I GET BACK TO YOU?

40:29.360 --> 40:31.730
GETTING BACK TO YOU
IN FIVE.

40:31.763 --> 40:34.566
[ Radio Static ]
[ Man ]
CARRIER TONE.

40:34.600 --> 40:37.469
- TRAFFIC SOUNDS.
- MY MAN--

40:37.503 --> 40:40.271
A GATE OPENING.
PLANTED OUR DEVICE
AS PLANNED...

40:40.305 --> 40:43.441
INSIDE THE CUSHIONS
OF THEIR AMBASSADOR'S
LIMOUSINE.

40:43.475 --> 40:48.279
THE LIMOUSINE AND GARAGE
WERE SWEPT BY THE IRANIANS
AND DECLARED CLEAN.

40:48.313 --> 40:51.983
NOW, WHEN THE AMBASSADOR
AND THE RUSSIAN
TAKE THAT DRIVE...

40:52.017 --> 40:56.488
AND DISCUSS THE ILLEGAL SALE
OF HEAVY-WATER NUCLEAR REACTORS
TO TEHRAN,

40:56.522 --> 40:59.124
I BELIEVE YOU WILL BE
PRIVY TO HIS CONVERSATION.

41:00.992 --> 41:03.529
[ Radio Static ]

41:03.562 --> 41:06.097
- [ Men Speaking
Foreign Language ]
- IT'S COMING ON NOW.

41:06.131 --> 41:08.867
PUT IT IN THE ROOM.

41:08.900 --> 41:11.102
- [ Men Continue
In Foreign Language ]
- [ Switch Clicks ]

41:11.136 --> 41:13.171
[ Continues, Louder ]
THAT'S THEM.

41:13.204 --> 41:15.373
MA'AM.

41:19.711 --> 41:23.114
- THAT'S WHY
THE PASSPORT'S FAKE.
- OH, IS HIS PASSPORT FAKE?

41:23.148 --> 41:25.684
THE ENTRY STAMP'S
SIX MONTHS OUT OF DATE.

41:25.717 --> 41:28.053
THIS IS THE CORRECT STAMP.

41:29.655 --> 41:32.691
YOU NEEDED YOUR MAN
BARRED FROM THE EMBASSY.

41:32.724 --> 41:35.994
- HOW ABOUT THAT?
- IS YOUR MAN REALLY A JEW?

41:37.596 --> 41:40.198
WHAT POSSIBLE CONCERN
IS THAT OF YOURS?

41:44.102 --> 41:46.872
[ Woman ]
LET'S GET A TRANSLATOR
IN HERE.

41:46.905 --> 41:51.977
THAT THING WE SPOKE OF--
IT'S OVER, MOLLY.

41:52.010 --> 41:55.013
YOU'RE SURE?
THOSE TWO PEOPLE
WE SPOKE OF,

41:55.046 --> 41:57.048
THOSE TWO PEOPLE
CONCERNED.

41:57.082 --> 41:59.384
AND AS I UNDERSTAND IT,

41:59.417 --> 42:04.656
THEY AGREED
THAT IT WAS WRONG,

42:04.690 --> 42:09.060
AND THAT-- THAT LUCKILY
THEY'D ENDED IT...

42:09.094 --> 42:11.496
WITHOUT DANGER--

42:11.529 --> 42:14.432
THAT THERE WAS NO DANGER,

42:14.465 --> 42:18.503
AND, UH, THE SITUATION
WAS A THING OF THE PAST.

42:18.536 --> 42:22.073
MM-HMM.
AND I WANT TO THANK YOU.

42:22.107 --> 42:24.175
THAT'S COMFORTING TO HEAR.

42:24.209 --> 42:27.445
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

42:27.478 --> 42:30.015
[ Beeps ]

42:30.048 --> 42:31.983
[ Knocking ]
[ Sighs ]

42:39.658 --> 42:41.827
COME ON OUT OF THE COLD,
COLONEL.

43:02.013 --> 43:04.349
[ Call And Response ]
* FIRED UP
FIRED UP *

43:11.322 --> 43:13.825
* TWENTY-SEVEN
FIRED UP *
